integrate the Fenwick tree more with our favorite little mrmriend <strong>b=
itset</strong>! What it actually means is, since we represent a set, we can=
 split its bitmask into blocks of 64 bits, each stored in a single <code cl=
ass=3D"tt">uint64_t</code>, and then Fenwick tree will be used to approxima=
